Statistics released by NTSA in 2018/2019 showed that 2,470 pedestrians accounted for the highest number of casualties through road accidents.The survey also noted that those who sustained serious injuries due to road accidents increased in 2019 by 48 per cent from 4,487 people in 2018 to 6,651 in 2019. More than 3,000 Kenyans have perished through road accidents since January, with the majority of the crashes attributed to careless driving.   
According to a report released by the National Police Service and National Transport and Safety Authority (NTSA), the death toll from accidents has risen by more than nine per cent compared to 2019.



