Assistant Inspector General of Police Robert Kitur, who is in charge of liaison, said 3,676 people had lost their lives on the roads by November, compared to 3,362 in 2019.
Mr Kitur said 95 per cent of the accidents are caused by careless drivers who hardly adhere to traffic rules since majority of them drive under the influence of alcohol.
According to Mr Kitur, speeding and disregard of road signs has also contributed to the increase in accidents.
Road accidents



