He also urged Kenyans to observe the Ministry of Health guidelines aimed at curbing the spread of Covid-19.
The police officer said crackdown has been intensified, particularly during this festive season, noting that drunk drivers will not be allowed to kill innocent Kenyans.
Statistics released by NTSA in 2018/2019 showed that 2,470 pedestrians accounted for the highest number of casualties through road accidents.
The annual crime report by the National Police Service, through a survey done in 2018, attributes the majority of accidents to speeding, drunk-driving, fatigue and carelessness of pedestrians.
The survey also noted that those who sustained serious injuries due to road accidents increased in 2019 by 48 per cent from 4,487 people in 2018 to 6,651 in 2019.
